summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Thirty-five and Fifty-six One- hundredths Dollars ($35.56) from the General Fund of the City of Seattle to pay the general taxes for the year 1907 assessed against those portions of Lots 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 27, 28, 29 and 30 in Block 2, and Lots 12, 13, 16, 25, 36, 37, 38 and 39 in Block 3, all in Hyde Park Addition to the City of Seattle, heretofore dedicated to the city for the extension of Thorndyke Avenue through said addition, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefore.
